        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-04T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-04T12:00:00-05:00" n="494"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d494">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">D. H. Miller</persName> to Colonel
                            <persName type="to">E. M. House</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="5" type="source" xml:id="d494fn5">This and the following telegram are
                        reprinted from David Hunter Miller, <hi rend="italic">My Diary at the
                            Conference of Paris, With Documents</hi> [1924–26], vol. <hi
                            rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 30 and 36.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-04T17:00:00+00:00">4
                            December, 1918—evening</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cravath thinks that final attitude of British as to indemnities is uncertain
                    largely owing to politics here but agrees with Davis that we will be in better
                    position if when negotiations begin we ask British French and Italians for a
                    definite formulation of their attitude on this and financial questions generally
                    in which their interest is more direct than our own. Nicholson [<hi
                        rend="italic">Nicolson</hi>] of Foreign Office told Cravath that French
                    memorandum on indemnities had been presented which Nicholson [<hi rend="italic"
                        >Nicolson</hi>] described as fantastic. I am planning to return to Paris
                    Saturday unless I receive other instructions.</p>
            </div>
